CLI
===
User configurate passthru session this way:
config terminal
int qam3/1.1
video udp <udp_port> passthru


IOS/LC message changes
======================

UDP_VALID:
  Adding the field process_mode in udp_valid_msg.
  Two defines: SESSION_PROCESS, SESSION_PASSTHRU
  If process_mode is SESSION_PASSTHRU, then num_entries must be 1.

OUTPUT_CONFIG:
  No new field in output_config_msg, but use num_es == 0
  to indicate passthru session


Data structure changes
======================
in_session (cc_input.h): add passthru flag (use 1 bit in mode).
vn_qam (cc_io.h): ?

CLI parser changes:
  cfg_int_output.h: program



Interaction
===========
CLI / configuration

-> IOS sends UDP_VALID message to configure udp port with passthru info

When passthru session starts, input will see this is passthru.
So it will skip PSI snooping, and send SESSION_START to IOS directly.

IOS will send OUTPUT_CONFIG to mux.
It will not send UPDATE_PMT/PAT/CAT to LC.
